### **network**

**Use-case:**Retrieve the**full interaction network**for one or more proteins.

```
https://string-db.org/api/tsv/network
    ?identifiers=STRING_ID
    &species=TAXID
    &required_score=700
    &limit=20

 ```

 Returns edges  
 Includes combined scores + evidence channels  
 You will use this for the graph visualization

## Retrieving best similarity hits between species

STRING internally uses the SmithWaterman bit scores as a proxy for protein homology. The original scores are computed by [SIMILARITY MATRIX OF PROTEINS](http://cube.univie.ac.at/resources/simap) (SIMAP) project. Using this API you can retrieve these similarity scores between your input proteins and proteins in all of the STRING's organisms. Only the best hit per organism for each protein will be retrieved.

There are many organisms in STRING, so expect thousands hits for each protein, however you can filter the results to the list of organisms of interest by using 'species_b' parameter.

#### Call:

```
https://string-db.org/api/[output-format]/homology_best?identifiers=[your_identifiers]

 ```

#### Available output formats:

| Format | Description |
| --- | --- |
| tsv | tab separated values, with a header line |
| tsv-no-header | tab separated values, without header line |
| json | JSON format |
| xml | XML format |

#### Available parameters:

| Parameter | Description |
| --- | --- |
| identifiers | required parameter for multiple items, e.g. DRD1_HUMAN DRD2_HUMAN |
| species | NCBI/STRING taxon (e.g. 9606 for human, or STRG0AXXXXX see: [STRING organisms](https://string-db.org/cgi/input.pl?input_page_active_form=organisms)). |
| species_b | a list of NCBI taxon identifiers seperated by " " (e.g. human, fly and yeast would be "9606 7227 4932" see: [STRING organisms](https://string-db.org/cgi/input.pl?input_page_active_form=organisms)). |
| caller_identity | your identifier for us. |

### **interaction_partners**

**Use-case:**Retrieve only**direct neighbors**of the protein (simpler, faster).

```
https://string-db.org/api/tsv/interaction_partners
    ?identifier=STRING_ID
    &species=TAXID
    &limit=100

 ```

 Best for 1-hop neighborhood visualizations  
 Great for simple side panels (list of partners)

request.description:
### **interaction_evidence**

**Use-case:** Retrieve evidence categories for a specific pair.

```
https://string-db.org/api/tsv/interaction_evidence
    ?identifiers=ID1
ID2
    &species=TAXID

 ```

Returns columns like:

- experiments
    
- curated databases
    
- text mining
    
- co-occurrence
    
- co-expression
    
- homology
    

 Use this to populate the Evidence breakdown panel  
 Perfect for edge tooltips or info popovers
